message.content:
The command does the following:

ssh -i "~/UserKey.pem": Specifies the private key file to use for authentication.
-C: Enables compression to reduce bandwidth usage during data transfer.
-L 25900:localhost:5900: Forwards a local port 25900 to the remote host's port 5900.
user@ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com: Connects to the specified user account on the given AWS EC2 instance.
